SampleMode: Sampling mode used for the bank.
Resolution: Number of samples cached for each entry in the given bank.
SampleRate: Number of samples cached for each entry in the given bank.
bBipolar:
Determines if output from curve/wavetable are to be clamped between
[-1.0f, 1.0f] (i.e. for waveform generation, oscillation, etc.)
or [0.0f, 1.0f] (i.e. for enveloping) when sampling curve/wavetable
